  "text": "## HTTP Health Check Endpoint Implementation Comparison\n\n### Kubernetes (github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes)\n**Endpoints:** `/healthz`, `/readyz`, `/livez`\n\nKubernetes implements a comprehensive pluggable health check system. The main framework is in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/healthz/healthz.go` with three separate handler installation functions: `InstallHandler` (for /healthz), `InstallReadyzHandler` (for /readyz), and `InstallLivezHandler` (for /livez).\n\n**Core Health Checks:**\n1. **PingHealthz** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/healthz/healthz.go) - Simple ping that always succeeds\n2. **LogHealthz** - Checks if logging is not blocked by verifying klog can flush within 2 minutes\n3. **NewInformerSyncHealthz** - Verifies that all Kubernetes informers (cache watchers) have completed initial synchronization\n4. **NewShutdownHealthz** - Checks if a shutdown signal has been received\n5. **ETcd Health Checks** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/options/etcd.go) - Direct connectivity checks to etcd storage backend, supporting both primary and override server configurations\n\nIn `cmd/kube-scheduler/app/server.go` (line 372-376), the scheduler registers health checks using `InstallHandler`, `InstallLivezHandler`, and `InstallReadyzHandler`. The framework in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/config.go` (line 398) establishes default checks of PingHealthz and LogHealthz.\n\nThe `/readyz` endpoint specifically includes ETcd readiness checks via `AddReadyzChecks` in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/options/etcd.go` (lines 367-369), which validates that the API server can communicate with its etcd backend.\n\n### Prometheus (github.com/prometheus/prometheus)\n**Endpoints:** `/-/healthy`, `/-/ready`\n\nPrometheus uses a simpler state-based approach in `web/web.go`. Rather than individual component checks, it maintains an overall `ReadyStatus` enum with three states: `NotReady`, `Ready`, and `Stopping`.\n\n**Health Check Implementation:**\n1. **/-/healthy** (web/web.go line 591) - Simple HTTP handler returning 200 OK with message \"{AppName} is Healthy\", supporting both GET and HEAD requests\n2. **/-/ready** (web/web.go line 598) - Wrapped by `testReady()` function which checks the current ReadyStatus state:\n   - Returns 200 OK if status is Ready\n   - Returns 503 Service Unavailable if status is NotReady or Stopping\n   - Sets `X-Prometheus-Stopping` header to indicate shutdown state\n\nThe `SetReady()` function (web/web.go line 642) transitions the server between states (NotReady -> Ready -> Stopping). The `testReady()` function (web/web.go line 659) wraps handler functions to enforce readiness state before allowing requests, making it a gating mechanism for query serving rather than a composite health check.\n\n### Grafana (github.com/grafana/grafana)\n**Endpoints:** `/healthz`, `/readyz`, `/livez`\n\nGrafana implements health checks through its embedded Kubernetes API server. In `pkg/services/apiserver/service.go` (lines 211-214), the health endpoints are registered as route groups that proxy to the underlying `genericapiserver.GenericAPIServer`.\n\nThe implementation registers these routes in `ProvideService()` with a proxy handler that:\n1. Waits for the service to be running via `AwaitRunning()`\n2. Delegates to the Kubernetes API server handler\n3. Inherits the full Kubernetes health check framework\n\nThis means Grafana's `/healthz`, `/readyz`, and `/livez` endpoints support the same pluggable health checks as Kubernetes, though the specific checks depend on which API server components are registered.\n\n## Key Architectural Differences\n\n**Kubernetes:** Pluggable, component-specific health checks (ping, logging, informers, etcd connectivity, shutdown signal). Each check can be excluded or grouped, with detailed failure reporting.\n\n**Prometheus:** State-based readiness (Ready/NotReady/Stopping) without granular component checks. Simpler model suitable for a single-purpose monitoring system.\n\n**Grafana:** Delegates to Kubernetes framework, inheriting its pluggable health check architecture while adding Grafana-specific components through the API server registration system."
}

